<title>USA: U.S. mortgage application volume rose in latest wk.</title>
<headline>U.S. mortgage application volume rose in latest wk.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>The volume of U.S. mortgage applications rose 12.3 percent in the week ended February 28, according to a Mortgage Bankers Association of America weekly survey.</p>
<p>Specifically, the volume of applications to refinance mortgages rose 3.6 percent in the latest survey week, while applications to purchase mortgages increased 15.8 percent.</p>
<p>The seasonally adjusted refinancing index fell 17.1 percent to 460.9 from 556.0 the previous week.</p>
<p>The purchase index fell 9.2 percent to 186.4 in the latest survey from 205.3 in the previous week.</p>
